n, s, e, w, u, d, flee             Go north, south, east, west, up, down, or flee from combat.
i, stat, skills                    List your inventory, character abilities, or skills.
kill, look (in), get, drop <obj>   Attack, look at (in), pick up, or drop <obj>. Look alone looks around.
get from <obj1> <obj2>             Get <obj2> out of <obj1>.
drop in <obj1> <obj2>              Put <obj2> into <obj1>.
-- Note that look in, get from, and drop in only work for objects on the ground.
stow, wield, hold, wear <obj>      Self explanatory I hope.
sneak, nosneak                     Start and stop sneaking.
short                              Toggle short descriptions.
quit                               Exit the mud.
swindle <mark> <item>              Try to swindle someone.
word <word> <intensity> <target>   Use a word of power. Intensity starts at 1. Omit the target and it is you!
use <obj>                          Use an item that you are holding or wielding.
read <obj>                         Read a message written on an object.
lock, unlock <obj>                 Lock, unlock a door or container.
prac <skill>                       Practice a skill.
-- Skills are perception, melee, stealth, steal, swindle, literacy, climbing, swimming, and magic.
The character ' followed by anything causes you to speak. For example, 'Hi!
